The paper deals with the problem of approximate consensus in dynamic networks, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the role of averaging algorithms in solving the problem, which is a topic related to social and information networks (cs.SI) and network science (cs.NI). The paper also considers synchronous and partially synchronous systems, which are topics related to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses time complexity and network models, which are topics related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
